text: Setobaudinia umbadayi is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Camaenidae. The species was found during an expedition led by Frank Koehler on the islands off the Kimberely Coast in 2017. It was amongst other species that were previously unknown to scientists found on the islands. ==References== * Bamford, M. 2017. http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-01-18/150-new-snail-species-discovered-on- kimberley-islands/8192326 umbadayi Category:Gastropods of Australia Category:Gastropods described in 2017
title: Setobaudinia umbadayi
